article.description: Ukari Figgs scored a season-high 16 points and Sylvia Crawley had 15 as the Portland Fire beat the Seattle Storm 70-63 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Figgs points Fire to second straight win
article.linkText: Fire's Figgs scores 16 in victory over cold-shooting Storm
article.story:
SEATTLE (AP) -- Ukari Figgs scored a season-high 16 points and
Sylvia Crawley had 15 as the Portland Fire beat the Seattle Storm
70-63 Tuesday night.

"She's getting more and more comfortable at the two position,'' Portland coach Linda Hargrove said. "It's been an adjustment for her and the team.''

   Alisa Burras added 12 points to help the Fire (2-4) to their
second straight victory.

Sue Bird had 19 points for Seattle (3-3), but was 6-of-17 from
the field. Lauren Jackson added 11 points.

"Give credit to Portland, but we didn't have the urgency and focus we needed,'' Seattle coach Lin Dunn said. "Every game, we are playing for a spot in the playoffs and we didn't respond to their aggressiveness''

Seattle was 8-of-28 from the field in the first half, and
finished at 36 percent. The Fire hit 49 percent of their shots.

   Bird, who came into the game second in the league in assists,
finished with three -- all in the second half.
